						<summary>

						<p>Parāntaka I: year 16: 922-23 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This records a gift of 180 sheep for burning two perpetual lamps in the temple of Perumāṉaḍigaḷ ‘who was pleased to stay’ at Tiruviśalūr, by one Arikulāntakap-Pallavaraiyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Māṟkāḷi the headman of Puliyūr.</p>						

						</summary>
